   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3eb7d353-def1-41ee-815e-20ae9c8fd210",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Final project - The housing project"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "325395ef-e507-4707-80d0-71ba62e06338",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Currently I am a 2nd year economics and finance student and last semester I had a very interesting course called \"Money, banking and financial markets\".\n",
    "In this course we talked a lot about how interest rates affect the world and how it works as a tool to make people spend more or less, whatever is best for the economy. \n",
    "This was a very interesting notion to me and in this project I aim to analyze how different interest rates affect the housing prices in developed and developing countries. \n",
    "Note: decided to categorize countries into developing vs developed as opposed to low vs mid vs high income,as data for low income ( countries in sub saharan africa are very very little and im left with reliable data for bsically developing and developed countries)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "67ec3bbd-02ad-4b47-a74a-3c887597319e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# The hypothesis I go into this project are the following:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fe2c0bbe-00f3-445c-8cb1-cc0f95a325f5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "H1: Interest rates affect housing prices equally across countries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d0292378-b3fa-45ed-93da-5d4c7cc2bb8c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "H2: The affect of interest rates is stronger in developed countries,than in developing countries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "87b794c9-41e3-4c16-aced-1691d90e63dc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# The steps I aim to make for this project:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "72daff6a-db1b-4bd1-9bb2-7860efcea48d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1. Gather and clean data about: Housing prices, Interest rates, Income levels and Inflation\n",
    "2. Clean and merge them into 1 big data set\n",
    "3. Divide data for developing and developed countries\n",
    "4. Analyze trends per group over the years\n",
    "5. Run a regression analysis on every group\n",
    "6. Compare and Analyze - confirm or deny H1 AND H2\n",
    "7. Summary of the project"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "101f51a1-eee2-40c2-9322-f681b4ad14de",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# DATA: Residential property prices - index , real(adjusted for inflation) , 2000 - 2025, quarterly ([Bis.data.org](https://data.bis.org/topics/RPP/data?data_view=table&rows=REF_AREA&cols=TIME_PERIOD&settings=asc%7Cdesc%7Cname&filter=FREQ%3DQ%255EUNIT_MEASURE%3D628%255EVALUE%3DR%255EYEAR%3D2000%257C2001%257C2002%257C2003%257C2004%257C2005%257C2006%257C2007%257C2008%257C2009%257C2010%257C2011%257C2012%257C2013%257C2014%257C2015%257C2016%257C2017%257C2018%257C2019%257C2021%257C2020%257C2022%257C2025%257C2024%257C2023))"
   ]
  },
